<article class="blog--container blog-preview">
<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2016/09/27/ready-your-java-8-reactive-apps-now-reactor-3-0-ga-is-out"> Ready your Java 8 Reactive apps now, Reactor 3.0 GA is out !</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/28f1e1df33de53d322cf42f4e6aec5ac?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/smaldini">Stephane Maldini</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2016-09-27 08:00:00.0">September 27, 2016</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2621" href="/blog/2016/09/27/ready-your-java-8-reactive-apps-now-reactor-3-0-ga-is-out#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>After more <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2016/02/16/reactor-2-5-a-second-generation-reactive-foundation-for-the-jvm">than a year of work</a>, <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2016/03/11/reactor-core-3-0-becomes-a-unified-reactive-foundation-on-java-8">multiple milestones</a> and fine tuning based on much feedback, I have the pleasure of announcing Reactor 3 General Availability. You will find Reactor Core 3.0.2.RELEASE on Maven Central.</p>
<p><a href="https://gitter.im/reactor/reactor?utm_source=badge&amp;utm_medium=badge&amp;utm_campaign=pr-badge&amp;utm_content=badge"><img src="https://badges.gitter.im/Join%20Chat.svg" alt="Join the chat at https://gitter.im/reactor/reactor"></a> <a href="https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/io.projectreactor/reactor-core"><img src="https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/io.projectreactor/reactor-core/badge.svg?style=plastic" alt="Reactor Core"></a> </p>
<h2><a href="#what-is-reactor-3" class="anchor" name="what-is-reactor-3"></a>What is Reactor 3 ?</h2>
<p>Reactor 3 provides a powerful and efficient <a href="http://reactive-streams.org">reactive</a> programming model for Java 8 based applications. The model builds upon the experience of both <em>Reactor 2</em> and <em>RxJava 1</em> and introduces a fluent way to compose asynchronous backpressure-ready event processing. <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2016/07/28/reactive-programming-with-spring-5-0-m1">Spring Framework 5 uses Reactor 3</a> to build and eventually expose a <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2016/09/22/new-in-spring-5-functional-web-framework">complete reactive story</a>. </p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2016/09/27/ready-your-java-8-reactive-apps-now-reactor-3-0-ga-is-out">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
